<div class="a2">To: <b>SampleMan</b></div>
<div class="b2">
    <i>I can only act on my best judgment.</i><p> With very much due respect, I understand your feeling. But in my position, I regularly carry a concealed deadly weapon, and must continually remind myself of the practical legal consequences of deploying that power of injury and death.<p> The rule is not to confuse your role as engaged endangered individual with that of post-event judge, jury, and executioner after the fact. To do so might amount to &quot;breaking into jail.&quot; <p>What you feel about it will have little, if any, bearing on how your actions will be judged if you wound, permanently disable, or kill an assailant as the event unfolds.<p> Defense is permitted, subsequent retributive or vindictive acts are not, AFIK.
<br clear="all"></div>
